        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Karankawa Indians.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p>Dear <persName>Colo</persName></p>

<p>It appears that about fifty of the <persName>Keronkiweys </persName>are Coming on to
attact the <placeName>lower Settlement</placeName> of this river and have said they would
devide into two <persName>Companys </persName>and perhaps one <persName>Company </persName>May Come up
the River as high as this <placeName>Settlement </placeName>we have determined to Collect
all our <persName>familys </persName>to one place perhaps here in order to guard them
which will take all the Men we Can raise in the <persName>upper Detachment
of this <placeName>district</placeName></persName> I think about <persName>forty Men from the <placeName>Brassos</placeName></persName> and
what Men there is in the <placeName>lower Settlement</placeName> on this River May be
enough to meet them which would be well to do as soon as possible-</p>
<p><date when="1824-08-25">August 25th 1824</date></p>

<p><persName>James Cummins</persName>    [Rubric]</p>
<p>[Addressed:] <persName>Col° Stephen F. Austin</persName> <placeName>San Felipe de Austin</placeName></p>

        </div1>
    </body>
